parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to repair or replace defective airbags can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident, and the lack of communication and resolution from dealerships and manufacturers can cause frustration and anxiety for vehicle owners.
symptoms: lack of communication from dealerships and manufacturers
and failure to deploy airbags in accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of replacement parts for airbag recalls can lead to prolonged periods of time where vehicles are not safe to operate, and owners are left without a solution.
symptoms: Dealerships and manufacturers unable to provide replacement parts
lack of communication about part availability
and prolonged wait times for repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Intrusion and Electrical System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water intrusion into the passenger compartment can cause electrical system failures, leading to safety risks, such as loss of headlights, brake lights, and instrument cluster malfunctions.
symptoms: Water leaks into the passenger compartment
headlights and brake lights not working
and mold growth in the interior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the instrument cluster can lead to loss of vital information, such as speed, fuel level, and engine temperature, which can increase the risk of accidents.
Failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the body control module can cause electrical system failures, leading to safety risks, such as loss of headlights, brake lights, and instrument cluster malfunctions.
symptoms: Body control module gets wet due to water intrusion

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of gas, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The fuel gauge drops to empty or gives erratic readings
even when the tank is full.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer can cause the driver to unknowingly exceed speed limits, leading to safety risks and potential legal issues.
symptoms: The speedometer gives inaccurate or erratic readings
sometimes showing high speeds even when the vehicle is stationary.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
sometimes accompanied by erratic throttle behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The gas tank filling issues can cause gas spills, leading to safety risks and environmental concerns.
symptoms: The gas tank will not accept fuel
or requires slow and careful filling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a loss of vehicle control, leading to safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: causing a loss of power to various systems

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose critical information, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The instrument cluster fails to provide accurate or any information
